The article discusses the actions taken by the Biden-Harris Administration to empower workers and promote economic growth. It highlights President Biden's commitment to being pro-worker and pro-union, with support for unions at its highest level in over 50 years. The article also mentions positive economic indicators such as increased income and wage gains for low-paid workers, as well as a low unemployment rate. Under Bidenomics, there is a focus on public and private investment in manufacturing and new industries to create good-paying jobs. The President is also advocating for fair pay and the right to join a union. In preparation for Labor Day, the administration is announcing new initiatives to invest in clean energy jobs, establish pathways to high-paying and union jobs, demonstrate the benefits of unions, and extend wage protections. These actions build on previous efforts to support workers and unions, including increasing wages, supporting the right to organize, expanding workforce development, and promoting equal employment opportunities.